The paper discusses the practical challenges of adversarial training, which is a topic related to machine learning and deep learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on hyperparameters and their impact on the effectiveness of adversarial training. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since adversarial attacks are often used in image classification tasks. The paper also discusses the use of hyperparameter optimization techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper deals with the security aspect of machine learning, it could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
